==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plumbing
<hw>Plumb"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art
of casting and working in lead, and applying it to building purposes;
especially, the business of furnishing, fitting, and repairing pipes for
conducting water, sewage, etc.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The lead or iron pipes, and other apparatus, used in
conveying water, sewage, etc., in a building.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plumbism</ent>⟦br⟧
